"```sql\nSELECT circuits.location, circuits.country\nFROM circuits\nJOIN races ON races.circuitId = circuits.circuitId\nJOIN results ON results.raceId = races.raceId\nJOIN constructors ON constructors.constructorId = results.constructorId\nWHERE constructors.name = 'Renault';\n```\n\nThis SQL query retrieves the locations and countries of circuits where the constructor \"Renault\" has participated in races. It joins the `circuits`, `races`, `results`, and `constructors` tables using the appropriate foreign key relationships to filter the results for the constructor \"Renault\"."